line_1: Thou art a Maid, and must not peep.
line_2: But, O my Muse, just Distance keep:

line_1: Thy silken locks that scantly peep,
line_2: With gold-tipp'd ends, where circles deep,

line_1: For could he ance but get a peep,
line_2: They may thank heav'n, auld Sam's asleep:

line_1: Till Light does thro' your Chamber Windows peep
line_2: While you on easy Beds may lie and sleep,
At their own beauty in the nether deep,

line_1: From ozier bowers the brooding Halcyons peep,
line_2: The Swans pursuing cleave the glassy deep,

line_1: Through which his half-wak'd Soul would faintly peep.
line_2: A comely full-spred Porter, swoln with Sleep:

line_1: Through which his half-wak'd Soul would faintly peep.
line_2: And in sweet Torpor he was plunged deep,

line_1: Through which his half-wak'd Soul would faintly peep.
line_2: Ne could himself from ceaseless Yawning keep;

line_1: And stars that through the pale sky peep!
line_2: And welcome, shadows dim and deep,

line_1: But from their silky veil there seemed to peep
line_2: The friendly curtain of indulgent sleep

line_1: And thro' the neighb'ring hedge I peep;
